In fact, 11% of U.S. citizens, i.e. 21 million people of voting age, do not have a photo ID issued by their state government.
In addition, there are no such identity cards for about five million new voters in 2012.
In addition, the purchase of the required identity card often costs more than a hundred dollars.
The new restrictions are disproportionately affecting mainly young people, members of minorities and low-income people.
